"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The use of `reset_index(drop=True)` after `apply` is incorrect because it is being applied to the result of the `apply` method, which returns a Series for each group. This can lead to misalignment of indices when assigning back to the DataFrame. Instead, the result should be concatenated back to the original DataFrame properly.\",\n  \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(level=0, drop=True)\"\n}"